author: Cliffe Oloo
title: What is the next course of action for Gen Zs after euphoric victory - The Standard
text: After a euphoric week of dictating the government’s agenda, thousands of young Kenyans who took to the street to oppose the punitive taxes were on Thursday unsure of the next course of action. Generation Z (Gen Z) were undecided whether to revel in their biggest triumph yet of forcing President William Ruto to [publicly disown](https://www.standardmedia.co.ke/national/article/2001497718/ruto-forced-to-eat-humble-pie-as-gen-z-protests-escalate) the Finance Bill he had so actively campaigned for or to press on and try to force the administration out of power. Using the X platform, participants spent hours arguing over the Road to Statehouse protests, a scenario that escalated to the formation of splinter groups amongst them. The exchange of views on different X Spaces came after President Ruto in his address to the nation, gave in to pressure and refused to assent to the Finance Bill, 2024. According to their itinerary, they were to proceed with the protests Thursday in a bid to occupy State House and demand President William Ruto to resign. However, one side of the faction of which Hanifa Adan was part of, advised against the “ill move’’ since it would result to bloodshed and loss of lives as witnessed during earlier protests. “Like we said, this has no leaders and everyone is deciding for themselves but I’m against marching to State House, we have lost a lot of people, can we honour them first?” she posted on X. Khalif Kairo, an entrepreneur who is vocal on the platform and was instrumental during the protests, urged the youth to take the President Ruto decision to withdraw the controversial bill as a win for them, and going forward, he urged them to consider Deputy President Rigathi Gachagua’s call for dialogue. “I feel like we have had a very big win. We should give dialogue a chance while allowing the President to act on our grievances,” he said. Meanwhile, a faction of Gen Z still determined to continue with the protests, accused some of them being paid to betray their cause. This group viewed the President’s move to [withdraw the Bill](https://www.standardmedia.co.ke/national/article/2001497974/house-to-consider-rutos-memo-after-recess-speaker-says) as too little too late and advocated for his removal. In a bid to convince everyone to hit the streets for the anti-government protests, some X Spaces participants pointed out the atrocities meted by police officers on peaceful and unarmed young Kenyans whose mistakes they say, was to ask the President why the political class was increasingly getting wealthier at the expense of the taxpayers. However, in their unity of purpose, a total of 31,070 people contributed Sh22.11million in support of the victims of violence meted on them during the process. The funds raised through a mobile money platform are expected to be used to clear hospital bills for those injured during the protests and for funeral arrangements for the fallen comrades. “The money is for burials and hospital bills. After paying the bills, the families will get the money too,” Adan posted. Stay informed. Subscribe to our newsletter

author: Seth Feiner
title: UPDATE: Man enters new plea in Willacoochee hit and run death
text:
DOUGLAS, Ga. (WALB) - A man charged in a fatal Coffee County hit and run in 2019 has changed his plea to guilty, according to court documents.
Dustin Jordan was originally charged in Febraury 2019 after he reportedly hit John Pond , 27, of Willacoochee, on Willacoochee Highway leading to his death. Video collected from nearby businesses helped law enforcement identify Pond.
Jordan originally pleaded not guilty on July 14, 2021, however, on June 12, 2024, he withdrew his last plea and pleaded guilty to homicide by vehicle -leaving the scene, court documents confirmed.
It is currently unclear if his plea to the charge of hit and run remains or has been changed.
Jordan will appear at a sentencing hearing on Aug. 7. This hearing comes after an agreement over five years of prison time was not agreed upon by both sides in the case, according to the Coffee County Superior Court Clerk’s Office.

author: IANS
title: Asian Stars Triumph in Legends League Cricket Finale | NewKerala.com
text:
Key Points
Rishi Dhawan's 83 runs sealed Asian Stars' championship victory
Indian Royals limited to 148 runs
Mehran Khan captained winning team
Massive crowd witnessed epic cricket showdown
Thousands of cricket enthusiasts from Udaipur, Nathdwara, and Rajsamand gathered to witness this historic match, with a large number of tourists from both domestic and international locations also attending as Asian Stars defeated Indian Royals by 6 wickets.
The winning team was honored by Madan Paliwal, Chairman of Miraj Group, League organizer Ravi Yadav, former BCCI selector Chetan Sharma, and other dignitaries.
Powerful Striker of the Match, Ishwar Pandey, Player of the Match, Rishi Dhawan, and Best Player of the Series, Mehran Khan, were all presented their awards. Guests also presented the shining trophy to Mehran Khan, the captain of the winning team, Asian Stars.
The final match began with Indian Royals winning the toss and opting to bat first. Sanjay Singh played a brilliant knock, scoring a crucial half-century for his team. Additionally, Yogesh Nagar (16 runs), VineetSaxena (15 runs), Mannan Sharma (14 runs), and Captain Faiz Fazal (11 runs) contributed with their individual scores. However, due to the effective bowling performance from Asian Stars, Indian Royals could only manage 148 runs for 10 wickets, setting a target of 149 runs for the Asian Stars.
During the mid-innings break, the stadium was filled with an atmosphere of patriotism and enthusiasm. Cricket fans waved a magnificent 120-meter-long tricolor, which became the most special attraction of the event. This historic moment filled the entire stadium with the spirit of patriotism.
Chasing the target, Asian Stars began their innings with a strong start. Experienced batsman RishiDhawan played a brilliant knock of 83 runs, leading his team toward victory. Raghav Dhawan (37 runs) and Kashyap Prajapati (15 runs) also made crucial contributions. Thanks to their strong partnership, Asian Stars clinched a 6-wicket victory and won the golden trophy of the Asian Legends League 2025 Championship.

author: Amanda Harding
title: Nick and Aaron Carter’s Sister Bobbie Jean Found Dead In Bathroom, Authorities Say ‘No Signs Of Foul Play’ | The Daily Wire
text: Streaming Now The decade's most triggering comedy Bobbie Jean Carter, 41, was discovered [dead](https://www.dailywire.com/topic/death) in the bathroom of her Florida home over the weekend. The sister of Nick and [Aaron Carter](https://www.dailywire.com/topic/celebrities) was found on Saturday, but new details are emerging regarding the manner of her death. The Hillsborough County Sheriff’s Office told [TMZ](https://www.tmz.com/2023/12/27/nick-aaron-carter-sister-bobbie-jean-carter-found-unresponsive-bathroom-dead-dies/) that first responders were dispatched to Bobbie’s Tampa residence on Saturday morning. “On December 23, 2023, Hillsborough County Fire rescue crews arrived at the home located… in Tampa, and they discovered a woman who later was identified as Bobbie Jean Carter,” a statement from the sheriff’s office said, per [Fox News](https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/bobbie-jean-carter-nick-aaron-carters-sister-dead-bathroom). “She was immediately transported to St. Joseph’s Hospital in Tampa, where she was declared dead by hospital medical staff at 8:02 a.m.” The outlet noted that Carter was on probation for [cocaine possession](https://www.dailywire.com/topic/drugs), but her roommate insisted that “she had not used any narcotics since her release from prison.” “No narcotics or personal paraphernalia were located in Ms. Carter’s room or bathroom. Deputies observed no signs of foul play,” the document stated. Deputies stayed with Carter’s 8-year-old daughter until relatives arrived, the outlet said. Bobbie Jean’s death is very similar to that of her brother, Aaron Carter, who was found dead in his bathtub in November 2022. The Los Angeles County Department of Medical Examiner-Coroner confirmed in April that the 34-year-old singer died from drowning after taking pills and huffing spray paint, as The Daily Wire previously [reported](https://www.dailywire.com/news/medical-examiners-release-official-cause-of-death-for-singer-aaron-carter). The report noted that Aaron’s cause of death was “due to the effects of difluoroethane (aerosol propellant found in spray cans) and alprazolam (commonly referred to as Xanax).” [CLICK HERE TO GET THE DAILYWIRE+ APP](https://onelink.to/dwapp) Aaron’s mother Jane Schneck blamed authorities for not investigating Carter’s death as a potential crime. She tried to raise public interest by publishing [graphic images](https://www.dailywire.com/news/aaron-carters-mom-releases-graphic-photos-of-his-death-scene-in-plea-for-police-assistance-we-want-answers) of her son’s death scene on her Facebook page, insisting that foul play was likely. “Aaron had a lot of death threats and many, many people who were making his life miserable,” the singer’s mother said at the time. Both Bobbie Jean and Aaron were siblings to Backstreet Boys singer Nick Carter. Their sister, Leslie Carter, [died in 2012](https://people.com/celebrity/leslie-carter-aaron-carters-sister-was-depressed-on-drugs/) at the age of 25 after going to sleep following a fall in the shower. Her death was also found to be drug related following years of substance abuse issues and depression, per People.

author: Iwan Stone
title: Man and woman killed after crash between car and ambulance transporting elderly patient | Daily Mail Online
text: A man and a woman have been killed in a crash between a car and a ambulance transporting an elderly patient. Both sustained injuries in the smash on the rural road near Newmarket, Suffolk, at 7.30pm on December 19. The marked transport ambulance had two passengers and a driver, while the blue Volkswagen Golf carried just the driver. Two people in the ambulance, the female driver and male passenger, sustained serious injuries and were taken to Addenbrooke’s Hospital for treatment. The second passenger, a woman, sustained minor injuries while the driver of the Golf also sustained serious injuries. The marked transport ambulance had two passengers and a driver, while the blue Volkswagen Golf carried just the driver. Pictured: File photo Two people in the ambulance, the female driver and male passenger, sustained serious injuries and were taken to Addenbrooke’s Hospital (pictured) for treatment Both sustained injuries in the smash on the rural road (pictured) near Newmarket, Suffolk, at 7.30pm on December 19 The driver of the Golf, who was in her 70s, has since died. One of the passengers in the ambulance, a man in his 90s, has also since died. Fire engines and ambulances attended the incident in mid December alongside police. Police are appealing for witnesses, who can call 101, quoting SC-19122023-302.
